<item>
            <title>[LU-110] Allow the use of a 2.0 MDS on a filesystem with a 1.8 disk format</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-110</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Version 1.8 uses a tunable named &quot;mdt.quota_type&quot; in order to store quota parameters in config, while version 2.x has a tunable named &quot;mdd.quota_type&quot; for the same purpose. This introduces incompatibility when trying to run a 2.x Lustre instance on top of a filesystem with a 1.8 disk format.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
        <key id="10420">LU-110</key>
            <summary>Allow the use of a 2.0 MDS on a filesystem with a 1.8 disk format</summary>
